<div id="review_2118539199" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2118539199" />
    <a title="grace  Sandefur " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71249505-grace-sandefur"><img alt="grace  Sandefur " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517554163p2/71249505.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2118539199?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="grace  Sandefur " class="user" itemprop="url" name="grace  Sandefur " href="/user/show/71249505-grace-sandefur">grace  Sandefur </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2118539199&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2118539199" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5089251225291562127">Oh. My. Gosh. I am a verrrrrry happy person right now. I have waited for this for so long. I lovvvvved this book. I thought the first half was a bit slow but other than that it was really pretty good. I wish that in the beginning of the book we could have seen more of Kirstyn and a little less of Aladdin. <br/> <br/>I didn’t like Grethel but I don’t think I was supposed to any way. I was just screaming in my head for her to back off and stop. I really loved Aladdin and I totally did not expect for there t</span>
  <span id="freeText5089251225291562127" style="display:none">Oh. My. Gosh. I am a verrrrrry happy person right now. I have waited for this for so long. I lovvvvved this book. I thought the first half was a bit slow but other than that it was really pretty good. I wish that in the beginning of the book we could have seen more of Kirstyn and a little less of Aladdin. <br /> <br />I didn’t like Grethel but I don’t think I was supposed to any way. I was just screaming in my head for her to back off and stop. I really loved Aladdin and I totally did not expect for there to be an Abu! I think Melanie did a fabulous job developing Aladdin’s character. I felt like we really knew who he was in the story. <br /><br />Kirstyn has been mentioned in other books as quiet and calm and I’m glad I got to see her. I feel like Melanie kind of put a reason behind her quietness in the story. Kirstyn said she felt a bit ignored and unimportant to her family, etc, and I just thought that it kind of told me a small part of why she may be quiet. <br /><br />So after she got saved and went home I was super excited to see her homecoming but that wasn’t in the book. She just sort of mentioned it. So I was a bit disappointed with that. Putting that aside, I really liked the parts her parents played in the story. I felt like because of her kidnapping that they were more involved. I might not always like that, but in this story I thought it was really nice and enjoyable. I also thought that after Kirstyn returned home Melanie did a really fantastic job of getting across how much the kidnapping affected Kirstyn. I really felt that she was scarred. And that part where Wolfgang grabbed her wrist, he was so sweet! In the other books I thought he was an annoying little brother but this showed another side of him and I just loved it! <br /><br />My favorite part of the book is like the last 50 pages or so. I loved it. Kirstyn and Aladdin finally have it all worked out and everybody is happy. I just wish that when Kirstyn’s female relatives (I’m assuming her all of sisters and sisters in law came to town and them and her mother did this) were dressing her for the wedding that there could have been a conversation between them. I really would have enjoyed that (Just a glimpse. Like a small conversation or situation that they may be involved in). I would love to see glimpses of the older, married siblings and their wives/husbands in the future books. I’ve also seen a lot of reviews on how people want to see Gabe and Rapunzel meet because Gabe felt to bad about her “death”; so I thought that would be pretty cool to see. I also would’ve loved to see the Gerstenberg family at the adoption of Abu. And I was sooo happy when I saw they had a baby and that they were adopting so many orphans and opening an orphanage! I really loved that Melanie incorporated adoption into the story. <br /><br />Over all this was a truly fantastic book that I really really enjoyed! I’ve recommended it to all my friends and I’m making them read it lol. I hope you continue adding to the Hagenheim Series for a long time and I can’t wait to see more books in the future!!!! <br /><br /><br />Oh yeah and this is off topic but I love the new little swirly thingies that indicate that it’s a new POV.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5089251225291562127" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


