<div id="review_2340519569" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2340519569" />
    <a title="Ashlee Clayton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22069247-ashlee-clayton"><img alt="Ashlee Clayton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1373428320p2/22069247.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2340519569?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashlee Clayton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashlee Clayton" href="/user/show/22069247-ashlee-clayton">Ashlee Clayton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2340519569&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2340519569" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10462092773527194326">Another win by Melanie Dickerson. Although I would never have guessed that the character of Aladdin would make an appearance in Hagenheim, Dickerson made his story come to life in a new and exciting way. Although at first I was hoping for an Arabian Princess as the heroine in this story, Kirstyn is a lovely character that you can&apos;t help but want to be friends with. Aladdin coming to terms with his past was a great storyline, as it shows how our current decisions, desires, and expectations are of</span>
  <span id="freeText10462092773527194326" style="display:none">Another win by Melanie Dickerson. Although I would never have guessed that the character of Aladdin would make an appearance in Hagenheim, Dickerson made his story come to life in a new and exciting way. Although at first I was hoping for an Arabian Princess as the heroine in this story, Kirstyn is a lovely character that you can't help but want to be friends with. Aladdin coming to terms with his past was a great storyline, as it shows how our current decisions, desires, and expectations are often dictated by the experiences we've gone through. <br />The character development in this book was so well written, I just didn't want the story to end, as it felt that I was saying goodbye to old friends. I appreciated how each character displayed their own weaknesses. Those weaknesses or insecurities helps you love them even more. <br /><br />The series has brought countless hours of wonderful reading, and I can't wait to see with Ms. Dickerson comes up with next!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10462092773527194326" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


